comments.body:
The patch looks good [~jianhe].  Would it be possible to add some documentation about what LOGDIR means, something like "LOGDIR is the directory that containers should use for logging".  Also, a minor nit - this line should be is too long and should be split:

{code}
  .getRelativeContainerLogDir(appId.toString(), ConverterUtils.toString(cId)), false);
{code}

{code}
+     * Directories that the container use for logging.
{code}
Should be "*Local* directories that the container *should* use for logging.".  It might also be good to mention that they come as a comma-separated list.

Otherwise, LGTM,

Please change the comment to be something like the following:
{code}
    /**
     * $LOG_DIRS Final, exported by NodeManager and non-modifiable by users.
     * Comma separate list of directories that the container should use for
     * logging.
     */
{code}

Also, it shouldn't export the base-directories. If the base log-dirs are /tmp/0/log-dir,/tmp/1/log-dir, it should export the env as /tmp/0/log-dir/app-id/container-id,/tmp/1/log-dir/app-id/container-id.

